<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/Forum9/HTML/001023.html">
<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=0 WIDTH="95%"><TR ><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#F0DCA0" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Postal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">      First off, is there a timer between times you can sleep?  Me, being a mage, can use up a lot of mana fast and when I teleport back to the bed I am using, it says something like This is no time to sleep.  Then I have to sit around a while and wait for it to let me to rest so I can get my mana back and then waist it in about 5 minutes trying to kill tough guys.  To me this is very frustrating, having to rest every 5 minutes and then waiting for me to be able to rest, unless there is no timer and I am doing something wrong.  Does it get any better off for a mage?  How do you other mages handle it?</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Fashtas</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">1) Potions are good! But potions where ever you can get them!<P>2) Alchemy is BETTER! A level 1 alchemy allows you to merge potions together (Merge Health and Mana of the same size for a restoration potion. A small Restoration potion heals MORE mana than a small mana potion alone)<P>3) Food is acceptable. Rabbit meat gives you mana but you have the same issue as the bed, you can only eat a certain amount in a set time (Also try FISH  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/smile.gif"> )<P>4) Use spells wisely. You will find a creature may need 100 flame bolts to kill but only 10 lighting. If 10 lightning costs MORE than 100 flame bolts (May do  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/smile.gif">) then it is cheaper to use the flame<P>Eventually mana will be the least of your worries!</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Postal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I wish they made it so that you slowly gain mana and even have a sit down key so you could gain mana and health even faster but would take more damage from enemies.  It is just boring to sleep, teleport in, kill 3 or 4 guys, move down a little bit, kill about 3 or 4 more, teleport back, wait around for you to be able to sleep, repeat...  Right now I am in the cursed abbey and there is one skeleton gaurdian and like 6 of his cronies.  The only thing I can do is throw out my 3rd meterstrike hurting some, kill others while I run around avoiding damage and then teleport back in to wait for mana.  Is there a better tactic for dealing with a situation like that?</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Fashtas</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If you are at the cursed abbey, you are really almost past the point where mana is a problem. There should be plenty of people to buy potions from and if you only use Restoration version, then you are refilling your mana bar completly for one potion<P>Your tactic of hit/run should also work fine, it's just your lack of potions/mana food that is the problem<P>Perhaps you should explore some more and find the traders in the area before continuing in the abbey? </FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Postal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yeah, I geuss that is what I should do.  Been trying to find chickens to kill since their meat give me mana.  Who has a good supply of mana potions and what herbs and stuff when used with alchemy make mana potions?</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kudarat</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">another way of recharging your mana and life is drinking from a pool of mana or pool of life. These pools are found in the dungeon located at the northern graveyard.You can acess the dungeon by a pit located soutthwest of the graveyard. <BR>Its reaally great to use these pools.<P>You can go to this graveyard quickly by teleporting to ars magicana or the graveyard.<P>So, if its not time to sleep and there's no potions or meat just visit the dungeon and have a drink. </FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Solitaire</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I am playing a Mage character, so here are a few tips from me :<P>- I set up base near the Ars Magicana Teleporter. I brought some straw that I made into a hay bed, and left it just next to the teleporter, and I left one of my own teleporter stones here. <BR>I also used to leave loot here to sell off later, and other items that I was collecting for quests but didn't need to use yet. <P>- Use potions & alchemy. I have Alchemy level 5, and I go on shopping sprees every now and then to the local potion vendors. <BR>There is a good potion vendor just South of Blake's General Store in Ars Mag, the other one I went to regulary was in Verstidis, in the SW corner of the map.<BR>I buy as many red, blue & white potions as possible, and all empty flasks. Then I mix all red & white potions together to make the appropraite level of Restoration. It seems that a minor restoration potion will restore half your mana, no matter how mush you have. <BR>It is also a good idea look at the goods of the other local vendors when you are on a shopping trip, Blake and some other vendors often have skill books for sale.<P>- While I am out exploring the world I will use the herbs and mushrooms I find to make potions. I haven't had to go out of my way to look for reagents to make potions, if I happen to come across a red mushroom in my path then I will bottle it  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>- Don't worry too much about chicken meat - it is much easier IMHO to buy or make potions than it is to find a chicken. <P>- So use your homemade or bought Restoration potions to refresh your mana. I will kill a few monsters, use a potion, kill a few monsters, use a potion, kill a few monsters until my mana is as close to zero as possible, then sleep next time. This means I am sleeping as often as I can to get back mana, and therefore using fewer potions. And also I am not sleeping soon after drinking a potion and wasting one !<P>- Get the monster ID skill early on. I didn't get it until right near the end and I must have wasted tons of mana. The skill helps you kill off all monsters very quickly  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>I hope this helps  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P><BR> </FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Solitaire</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sorry I forgot to answer your actual questions .....<P>Blue herbs and blue mushrooms make mana potions  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/smile.gif"><BR>Just drag a potion bottle out of your inventory over the mushroom or herb.<P>At level one you can make minor potions and mix minor potions together (I think). I am not sure what the levels are afterwards.<P>Oh, and if you end up mixing lots of red & blue potions together one after the other - turn your speakers off !!<BR>My character comments EVERY TIME you mix 2 potions together.<BR>It can get a bit annyoing after the 20th time hearing her say "Superb!", in a way that sounds like she is surprised that it actually worked - even through she has done it 100's of times before  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/wink.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Serops</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well, Solitaire gave some excellent advice.  Potions are key to aleviating a lot of the frustration you may encounter when playing a mage.  Alchemy lvl 3 is really all you need (the normal sized restoration potions restore 100% of health and mana).  Know creature is essential.  Also don't forget to pump up intelligence.  My mage puts at least 2 points (often 3) per level in intelligence.  I've largely ignored agility. True I can't hit anything in melee and if things get close I'm easy to hit, but most creatures don't get close and I've been working on strength so I can wear decent armor (=damage reduction).  Also make sure you develop at least one skill that slows creatures down (burning wall, blind, limbs of lead).  Mana charms are also your best friends.  A silver mana charm adds 80 mana, get a couple and it really adds up (my lvl 25 mage has over 650 mana).  The magic shop in Ars Magicana often sells silver charms, keep an eye out. <p>[This message has been edited by Serops (edited 30-10-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Postal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thanks for all the help so far.  Does it help any to summon monsters?  Do they distract monsters long enough for me to focus my attacks on the really powerfull monster?</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Postal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I also noticed that a lot of spells require the monster to have a certin resistence to spirit.  Are those spells worth getting or is monster resistence to spirit not that common?</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Momaw</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I'm making my second run through the game as a mage character. I found something that helps immensely, at least at the beginning, is a weapon that has Mana Drain.  I've seen two different weapons with it, both "of the Mind Feeder", a scythe and a long-dagger. Every hit is a +6 to my mana  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/smile.gif"> Now if I could just find a weapon that has both Mana Drain and Life Leech...</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</IFRAME>
